_exptl_crystal_grow.pdbx_details    
;His6-tagged GgUOX at approx. 22 mg/ml in 50 mM Tris-HCl pH 8.0, 10 mM NaCl, 1 mM TCEP-HCl was incubated with a 20-fold molar excess of AZA. Crystals were obtained by mixing the protein with 0.8M K/Na tartrate tetrahydrate, 0.1 M HEPES pH 7.5  using a 1:1 ratio. Crystals were transferred into cryoprotective solutions supplemented with 100 mM H2O2 and devoid of the TCEP-HCl reducing agent for approximately 15 minutes prior to cryocooling in liquid nitrogen.
